Description: Fragment of round handle at neck join from a Brindisi pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pale beige-buff; white and red inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Latin inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Hanno. cf. Desy, Ph., Les timbres amphoriques de l'Apulie republicaine (Oxford 1989) 180. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 122, 9.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1297)
